# Code owners — mandatory reviewers for changes.
#
# Enforcement requires enabling "Require review from Code Owners" in the branch
# protection rules for `main` (this file alone only assigns reviewers).
#
# High-leverage / security-sensitive surfaces are called out explicitly so a PR
# that touches them can't merge without a maintainer's review:
#   - skills/**            ships behavioral instructions to downstream AI agents;
#                          a malicious edit is a prompt-injection supply-chain
#                          attack on every consumer (invisible to code scanners).
#   - .github/workflows/** the CI/release pipeline (signing, provenance, tokens).
#   - .goreleaser.yaml     the release build + artifact definitions.
#   - docs/THREAT-MODEL.md, docs/SECURITY.md  the security contract.

# Default owner for everything.
*                       @arenzana

# Explicit, security-critical paths (kept last so they win over the catch-all).
/skills/                @arenzana
/.github/               @arenzana
/.goreleaser.yaml       @arenzana
/docs/THREAT-MODEL.md   @arenzana
/docs/SECURITY.md       @arenzana
